originalText.text:
BEWARE OF OLDER KAREN/NEW MANAGER - rude/discrimination towards long term customer

Yesterday I went in to do my usual monthly cash deposit from a tenant and get a money order sent to the rental office out of state. There was an older Karen working who completely interrupted my teller mid-transaction and told me that $6000 was "too much" to deposit and get a money order for the same day. I  knew this was a lie, commercial banks are required to have money in reserve to cover money orders/withdrawals.

I went to a diff TD branch a few blocks over and got the money order with no issue, they were in disbelief that the other woman had refused.

I am no longer comfortable going into this branch. All the other staff is very nice incl a younger woman with short hair and glasses. The whole experience made me uncomfortable, embarrassed and wasted extra time I didn't have that day to get the check made!

I don't know why someone would even be hired who either knows nothing about reserve requirements or makes a habit of lying to long term customers??

originalText.text: The Manager named Diana in this branch is very RACIST and very pushy, i was trying to deposit some cash last night around 6PM and she keeps on telling me to use the machine, i went to the teller and the teller said that the vault is closed, then Diana came to me again and said that the money counter machine is broken, really? that branch only has 1 money counter machine? The manager is very disrespectful and very RACIST! Not sure why she still there and why the teller are trained that way. Be professional! you're representing a company that has good reputation. I hope that TD Bank management will hear and know this complain, I will be waiting for your reply.

originalText.text: Has nice staff, but the bank network is systematically not honest. The bank promised me that will pay some money as a bonus for being referred by someone to open an account. Then after several months they refused to do what they promised.  Even worse, I suddenly noticed that they started to charge me $50 every month for 3 monthsas maintenance fee, while I wasn't eligible for that. After discussing, they get 2 months charges back, and erased any document. So my $50   was gone! Rediculous!
